comments: Grade based on lab manual write up. Graders grade the write up very harshly. Be meticulous. Write an inconceivable amount about the dullest experiments. Attempt survival.

It is extremely hard to get past his thick accent so it\'s almost best to ignore him because you can get started with out his slow repetitive instructions. The class is long and the grade is based entirely on the write up, so hurry through the experiment and do the write up. Don\'t ask stupid questions cause he will male fun of you.

Fantastic guy, he is incredibly sarcastic. People who think that he is actually mean are just stupid. If you ask questions he will help you until you get it right. He is also incredibly smart, just look at what his doctorate is in!
COMPLETELY AVOID HIM, CAN\'T UNDERSTAND A WORD HE SAYS... YELLS AT YOU WHEN YOU DON\'T UNDERSTAND... JUST AVIOD, PLAIN AND SIMPLE...

I like him! simply because he explains everything before you start your lab. he writes down all the derivation that contributes to many points for the lab. Sometimes you can\'t really understand what he says, but he gives good grades. i got like a 97% avg for each lab! not much effort!

AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!! Between the fact that you nearly can\'t understand a word that comes out of his mouth, is completely useless outside of class, and changes the homework a night or two before it\'s due, he really was one of my worst professors I had in my first year. AVOID!!!

I had him for lab. You have to make a committed effort to understand half of what he says; I laughed so I wouldn\'t cry. He\'s very strict when it comes to grading that lab notebook, so make sure to write everything. Everything!
Very nice guy, the lab is tolerable. Talks a lot before he lets you start the lab, but he explains EVERYTHING. Pretty decent lab teacher.

Avoid this guy like the plague, he\'s an awful teacher. Can\'t understand a word he speaks, changes the homework literally the day before it is due, and his test are extremely long and difficult. AVOID!!!
He\'s difficult to understand and makes many errors while teaching. He also changes the homework assignments last-minute. Try you very best not to take his class.
He is very hard to understand and speaks Pakistanglish. Gets confused in class and changes the homework assignments. Do not take his class.
Not a difficult grader, but also completely impossible to understand or learn anything from.
sometimes his accent is difficult to understand. lots of writing. likes to take a long time to explain lab. knows what his is talking about will help if asked.
he is very nice , and very helpful .
